In the following code segment,  words  is an  ArrayList  of two or more  String  objects.
 int prev = words.get(0).length(); 
int count = 0; 

for (int j = 1; j < words.size(); j++) 
{ 
   int curr = words.get(j).length(); 
   if (curr == prev)
   { 
      count += 1; 
   } 
   prev = curr; 
}
